if I'm not mistaken,
or Adelaide.

00:29:04.390 --> 00:29:06.400 align:middle line:84%
And they said, let's
find out if it's true.

00:29:06.400 --> 00:29:09.100 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you can't really make
this stuff up because if you do,

00:29:09.100 --> 00:29:09.900 align:middle line:90%
you die.

00:29:09.900 --> 00:29:10.700 align:middle line:90%
It's desert.

00:29:10.700 --> 00:29:12.220 align:middle line:90%
There are no redeeming features.

00:29:12.220 --> 00:29:15.220 align:middle line:84%
They found that if you
used these special tracks,

00:29:15.220 --> 00:29:18.270 align:middle line:84%
these invisible energy lines,
to get from sacred space

00:29:18.270 --> 00:29:22.830 align:middle line:84%
to sacred space, the margin
of error is less than 3%.

00:29:22.830 --> 00:29:26.470 align:middle line:84%
When you take these lines to
go to non spiritual places,

00:29:26.470 --> 00:29:28.725 align:middle line:90%
the margin of error is over 67%

00:29:28.725 --> 00:29:31.350 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Didn't they have that
experiment with some Aboriginal

00:29:31.350 --> 00:29:31.730 align:middle line:90%
people?

00:29:31.730 --> 00:29:32.310 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yeah.

00:29:32.310 --> 00:29:32.730 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:29:32.730 --> 00:29:34.450 align:middle line:84%
And so they could
go right there.

00:29:34.450 --> 00:29:36.550 align:middle line:84%
They could make a beeline
for the sacred site.

00:29:36.550 --> 00:29:37.210 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yeah, exactly.

00:29:37.210 --> 00:29:37.690 align:middle line:90%
And they'll just be--

00:29:37.690 --> 00:29:39.010 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: But a random site, no.

00:29:39.010 --> 00:29:39.810 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: No.

00:29:39.810 --> 00:29:41.080 align:middle line:90%
They'll be hearing the land.

00:29:41.080 --> 00:29:43.120 align:middle line:90%
The energy field is open.

00:29:43.120 --> 00:29:45.730 align:middle line:84%
They're taking in all the
subtleties of the landscape.

00:29:45.730 --> 00:29:47.458 align:middle line:90%
Anybody can do this, by the way.

00:29:47.458 --> 00:29:48.750 align:middle line:90%
Again, it's like driving a car.

00:29:48.750 --> 00:29:50.420 align:middle line:84%
The more you do it,
the more you become

00:29:50.420 --> 00:29:53.460 align:middle line:84%
attached to the actual
invisible world around you.

00:29:53.460 --> 00:29:54.780 align:middle line:90%
And it's very beneficial.

00:29:54.780 --> 00:29:56.780 align:middle line:90%
So they just expand their field.

00:29:56.780 --> 00:30:00.530 align:middle line:84%
And they're aware of everything,
sounds and subtleties

00:30:00.530 --> 00:30:03.300 align:middle line:84%
in the landscape and of course,
invisible people as well.

00:30:03.300 --> 00:30:05.580 align:middle line:84%
And that's what guides
them through the landscape.

00:30:05.580 --> 00:30:08.270 align:middle line:84%
I mean, 30 years ago
when I was doing this,

00:30:08.270 --> 00:30:09.608 align:middle line:90%
I hadn't started dowsing yet.

00:30:09.608 --> 00:30:12.150 align:middle line:84%
And then people were saying,
oh, you don't need dowsing rods,

00:30:12.150 --> 00:30:13.230 align:middle line:90%
you don't need pendulums.

00:30:13.230 --> 00:30:15.510 align:middle line:84%
You can actually do this
if you do it long enough.

00:30:15.510 --> 00:30:18.243 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, OK, crazy
person, now I can sit here

00:30:18.243 --> 00:30:20.160 align:middle line:84%
and I can tell you where
the energy lines are,

00:30:20.160 --> 00:30:21.620 align:middle line:84%
what color they are,
where they're moving to,

00:30:21.620 --> 00:30:22.910 align:middle line:90%
what polarity they are.

00:30:22.910 --> 00:30:24.570 align:middle line:90%
It's second nature to me.

00:30:24.570 --> 00:30:26.180 align:middle line:90%
And anybody can do this.

00:30:26.180 --> 00:30:28.400 align:middle line:84%
It's just about expanding
your own energy field

00:30:28.400 --> 00:30:30.360 align:middle line:84%
and being in contact
with everything else.

00:30:30.360 --> 00:30:34.490 align:middle line:84%
And it comes in very useful,
not just for survival, but also

00:30:34.490 --> 00:30:37.140 align:middle line:84%
for developing
your own intuition,

00:30:37.140 --> 00:30:40.160 align:middle line:84%
as I call it, and also to
get the right winning lottery

00:30:40.160 --> 00:30:42.450 align:middle line:84%
numbers, which
happens so regularly,

00:30:42.450 --> 00:30:45.190 align:middle line:84%
but because it's
not part of my--

00:30:45.190 --> 00:30:47.090 align:middle line:84%
my path in life to
win the lottery,

00:30:47.090 --> 00:30:50.480 align:middle line:84%
to become rich, that I get
the numbers every single year.

00:30:50.480 --> 00:30:52.510 align:middle line:84%
And of course,
something happens, just

00:30:52.510 --> 00:30:53.720 align:middle line:90%
when I go to play the number.

00:30:53.720 --> 00:30:56.053 align:middle line:84%
The gates are already closed
because someone in the shop

00:30:56.053 --> 00:30:58.190 align:middle line:84%
recognizes him and says,
hi, how have you been?

00:30:58.190 --> 00:30:58.510 align:middle line:90%
And I thought--

00:30:58.510 --> 00:31:00.175 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I can't tell you
how many people do this.

00:31:00.175 --> 00:31:01.930 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: We have a group
actually in England.

00:31:01.930 --> 00:31:02.950 align:middle line:90%
We get together every--

00:31:02.950 --> 00:31:04.690 align:middle line:84%
when we get together
and say, how much money

00:31:04.690 --> 00:31:05.690 align:middle line:90%
have you lost this year?

00:31:05.690 --> 00:31:06.830 align:middle line:90%
Oh, I've lost 60 million.

00:31:06.830 --> 00:31:07.120 align:middle line:90%
Oh.

00:31:07.120 --> 00:31:08.100 align:middle line:90%
And we have a good laugh.

00:31:08.100 --> 00:31:08.450 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: [LAUGHS]

00:31:08.450 --> 00:31:10.240 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And just
before I left for a trip

00:31:10.240 --> 00:31:12.618 align:middle line:84%
to New Zealand a few months
ago, I got it in my head,

00:31:12.618 --> 00:31:13.910 align:middle line:90%
oh, you need to buy the ticket.

00:31:13.910 --> 00:31:14.800 align:middle line:90%
I thought, all right.

00:31:14.800 --> 00:31:16.950 align:middle line:84%
And then I got busy
packing, and I thought, damn

00:31:16.950 --> 00:31:20.240 align:middle line:84%
it, I should have got the
ticket, is only up the road.

00:31:20.240 --> 00:31:22.115 align:middle line:84%
And then I was in New
Zealand a week later

00:31:22.115 --> 00:31:24.740 align:middle line:84%
and I thought, let me just check
to see if the numbers came up.

00:31:24.740 --> 00:31:25.670 align:middle line:90%
Yes, they came up.

00:31:25.670 --> 00:31:28.840 align:middle line:84%
I won the lottery
again in the shop, just

00:31:28.840 --> 00:31:31.340 align:middle line:84%
up the road where I would have
got my ticket, by the way.

00:31:31.340 --> 00:31:33.020 align:middle line:90%
And here's the really sad part.

00:31:33.020 --> 00:31:35.810 align:middle line:90%
$1.2 billion.

00:31:35.810 --> 00:31:37.820 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Oh, Freddy,
you would have wasted it.

00:31:37.820 --> 00:31:38.020 align:middle line:90%
You would have--

00:31:38.020 --> 00:31:40.472 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And I'm still
driving a 20-year-old car.

00:31:40.472 --> 00:31:41.680 align:middle line:90%
I mean, what is up with that?

00:31:41.680 --> 00:31:43.370 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well,
what's up with that.

00:31:43.370 --> 00:31:45.822 align:middle line:84%
You're not supposed to
be in control of 1.2

00:31:45.822 --> 00:31:47.030 align:middle line:90%
however many billion dollars.

00:31:47.030 --> 00:31:47.950 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: I've got
to work hard for--

00:31:47.950 --> 00:31:48.810 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You've
got to keep working.

00:31:48.810 --> 00:31:50.935 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: But the point is that
it expands your natural ability.

00:31:50.935 --> 00:31:51.595 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It does.

00:31:51.595 --> 00:31:53.100 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And that's
how you use it.

00:31:53.100 --> 00:31:55.100 align:middle line:84%
You do it for your own
development, for whatever

00:31:55.100 --> 00:31:56.520 align:middle line:90%
it is you came here to do.

00:31:56.520 --> 00:31:57.930 align:middle line:90%
And that's the other benefit.

00:31:57.930 --> 00:32:00.483 align:middle line:84%
You begin to discover
the purpose of your soul.

00:32:00.483 --> 00:32:03.150 align:middle line:84%
And that's something that Plato
and Pythagoras were very big on.

00:32:03.150 --> 00:32:06.320 align:middle line:84%
And they said, and I quote,
"interacting with portals

00:32:06.320 --> 00:32:10.390 align:middle line:84%
or the sacred places in Greece
is what shaped our metaphysical

00:32:10.390 --> 00:32:11.190 align:middle line:90%
doctrine."

00:32:11.190 --> 00:32:13.002 align:middle line:84%
Now, for Plato to
say that tells me

00:32:13.002 --> 00:32:15.210 align:middle line:84%
that he actually experienced
something very profound,

00:32:15.210 --> 00:32:17.510 align:middle line:84%
but he wasn't supposed to
talk about it because you

00:32:17.510 --> 00:32:20.030 align:middle line:84%
had a vow of silence
because you weren't supposed

00:32:20.030 --> 00:32:21.750 align:middle line:84%
to tell about your
personal experience,

00:32:21.750 --> 00:32:24.860 align:middle line:84%
because it would shape the
experience of somebody else.

00:32:24.860 --> 00:32:27.660 align:middle line:84%
But your purpose in life
is different to mine.

00:32:27.660 --> 00:32:29.790 align:middle line:90%
I can't color your experience.

00:32:29.790 --> 00:32:31.230 align:middle line:84%
I can't prejudice
your experience.

00:32:31.230 --> 00:32:33.900 align:middle line:84%
So I can just say these are
the mechanics behind it.

00:32:33.900 --> 00:32:34.820 align:middle line:90%
Now you have to go--

00:32:34.820 --> 00:32:36.000 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You will have
your own experience.

00:32:36.000 --> 00:32:37.153 align:middle line:90%
So let me ask you about--

00:32:37.153 --> 00:32:39.570 align:middle line:84%
I want to get-- there are so
many places I want to get to.

00:32:39.570 --> 00:32:41.610 align:middle line:84%
I already mentioned
we went to Sardinia.

00:32:41.610 --> 00:32:46.590 align:middle line:84%
Yes, there were mounds that
had their ceremony for, what,

00:32:46.590 --> 00:32:49.320 align:middle line:84%
7-8,000 years that had
been going on there,

00:32:49.320 --> 00:32:51.440 align:middle line:84%
also that are open
to the public.

00:32:51.440 --> 00:32:53.180 align:middle line:90%
Giants inhabited the land.

00:32:53.180 --> 00:32:54.210 align:middle line:90%
Giants tombs.

00:32:54.210 --> 00:32:59.330 align:middle line:84%
And we got to experience again
that beehive dome like energy

00:32:59.330 --> 00:33:01.458 align:middle line:84%
in these places,
which was exquisite.

00:33:01.458 --> 00:33:03.000 align:middle line:84%
But if anyone wants
to know about it,

00:33:03.000 --> 00:33:04.560 align:middle line:84%
they can go watch
that series on Gaia.

00:33:04.560 --> 00:33:05.030 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Absolutely.

00:33:05.030 --> 00:33:06.738 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So we won't
need to go into it.

00:33:06.738 --> 00:33:09.620 align:middle line:84%
One place I lived for
years and people come

00:33:09.620 --> 00:33:12.300 align:middle line:84%
to from all around the
world is Sedona, Arizona.

00:33:12.300 --> 00:33:15.120 align:middle line:84%
Pretty accessible for most
people within the US anyway.

00:33:15.120 --> 00:33:18.685 align:middle line:84%
Did you ever have any unique
experiences in Sedona?

00:33:18.685 --> 00:33:20.390 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Yeah, but
none of the places

00:33:20.390 --> 00:33:22.550 align:middle line:84%
that they have on the
local map, which is usually

00:33:22.550 --> 00:33:23.965 align:middle line:90%
marked by jeep companies.

00:33:23.965 --> 00:33:24.270 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, yeah.

00:33:24.270 --> 00:33:24.710 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:33:24.710 --> 00:33:26.520 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: The more jeep companies
that appear are doing it,

00:33:26.520 --> 00:33:27.645 align:middle line:90%
the more portals there are.

00:33:27.645 --> 00:33:29.610 align:middle line:84%
So you've got to be
very careful about this.

00:33:29.610 --> 00:33:31.440 align:middle line:84%
You've got to trust
your own gut feeling.

00:33:31.440 --> 00:33:33.450 align:middle line:84%
There was one actually,
it was a trail.

00:33:33.450 --> 00:33:37.280 align:middle line:84%
I can't believe how busy
Sedona has become in 25 years

00:33:37.280 --> 00:33:38.370 align:middle line:90%
since I first went there.

00:33:38.370 --> 00:33:39.990 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I moved
away six years ago,

00:33:39.990 --> 00:33:41.692 align:middle line:84%
and I hear it's
really, really busy.

00:33:41.692 --> 00:33:44.150 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: So people that tend
to go to the usual places like

00:33:44.150 --> 00:33:46.267 align:middle line:84%
cathedral rock or bell
rock is a classic--

00:33:46.267 --> 00:33:47.100 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Beautiful.

00:33:47.100 --> 00:33:49.040 align:middle line:84%
But no, you've got to
get off where they're--

00:33:49.040 --> 00:33:50.570 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: --my nice and quiet.

00:33:50.570 --> 00:33:53.910 align:middle line:84%
And I got this lovely
little map on my phone.

00:33:53.910 --> 00:33:55.830 align:middle line:84%
Finally, I found a
good use for my phone.

00:33:55.830 --> 00:33:59.130 align:middle line:84%
It gives me highly detailed
tracks on the landscape.

00:33:59.130 --> 00:34:01.763 align:middle line:84%
And I found 50,000 people going
over there and I'm feeling,

00:34:01.763 --> 00:34:02.930 align:middle line:90%
but I want to go over there.

00:34:02.930 --> 00:34:04.110 align:middle line:90%
Oh, there's a track.

00:34:04.110 --> 00:34:05.670 align:middle line:90%
And it's not very well known.

00:34:05.670 --> 00:34:06.900 align:middle line:90%
So I just follow that.

00:34:06.900 --> 00:34:09.172 align:middle line:84%
The three hours I
was in complete bliss

00:34:09.172 --> 00:34:11.630 align:middle line:84%
without taking drugs, which
actually you shouldn't be doing

00:34:11.630 --> 00:34:13.716 align:middle line:84%
at these places because
it gets in the way

00:34:13.716 --> 00:34:14.674 align:middle line:90%
of the pure experience.

00:34:14.674 --> 00:34:15.716 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, absolutely.

00:34:15.716 --> 00:34:17.340 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: I found
my own sacred cave,

00:34:17.340 --> 00:34:20.027 align:middle line:84%
and I sat there for two
hours, away with the fairies,

00:34:20.027 --> 00:34:21.360 align:middle line:90%
literally away with the fairies.

00:34:21.360 --> 00:34:24.320 align:middle line:84%
And they came back with a
whole set of notes of stuff

00:34:24.320 --> 00:34:26.460 align:middle line:90%
that I hadn't even asked for.

00:34:26.460 --> 00:34:28.830 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, this has the
makings of a new project.

00:34:28.830 --> 00:34:31.250 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, I just went there to
connect with the landscape

00:34:31.250 --> 00:34:33.690 align:middle line:84%
and see if I can learn
something new and boom!

00:34:33.690 --> 00:34:34.530 align:middle line:90%
There you have it.

00:34:34.530 --> 00:34:37.250 align:middle line:84%
So you've got to trust your
own sort of feeling when you're

00:34:37.250 --> 00:34:40.089 align:middle line:84%
on the land and just follow that
guidance and see where it goes.

00:34:40.089 --> 00:34:40.889 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I agree.

00:34:40.889 --> 00:34:44.820 align:middle line:84%
And in Sedona, not to advertise
for more tourists to Sedona,

00:34:44.820 --> 00:34:48.210 align:middle line:84%
but it seems that everything
is quite available.

00:34:48.210 --> 00:34:50.310 align:middle line:84%
And I mean, I remember
before I even moved there,

00:34:50.310 --> 00:34:53.297 align:middle line:84%
going there and going to
one of the sites off road,

00:34:53.297 --> 00:34:54.630 align:middle line:90%
you have to find your way to it.

00:34:54.630 --> 00:34:57.620 align:middle line:84%
But in any event,
I remember being

00:34:57.620 --> 00:35:02.210 align:middle line:84%
in the dwellings that the Native
American populations of far past

00:35:02.210 --> 00:35:04.290 align:middle line:90%
had been in and they were there.

00:35:04.290 --> 00:35:06.360 align:middle line:84%
You could see them
walking around.

00:35:06.360 --> 00:35:10.490 align:middle line:84%
I actually went into a
chamber and was witnessing.

00:35:10.490 --> 00:35:13.430 align:middle line:84%
It shocked me at the time, but
like a 12-year-old girl giving

00:35:13.430 --> 00:35:14.988 align:middle line:90%
birth and such.

00:35:14.988 --> 00:35:16.780 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's all right
there and available.

00:35:16.780 --> 00:35:17.795 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: They're
never left away.

00:35:17.795 --> 00:35:18.560 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It never left.

00:35:18.560 --> 00:35:19.135 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: They never left.

00:35:19.135 --> 00:35:19.730 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No.

00:35:19.730 --> 00:35:20.980 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: I mean, the Sinagua--

00:35:20.980 --> 00:35:21.980 align:middle line:90%
I love the Sinagua.

00:35:21.980 --> 00:35:24.350 align:middle line:84%
And they're just South
in Montezuma's castle.

00:35:24.350 --> 00:35:25.320 align:middle line:90%
Terrible name again.

00:35:25.320 --> 00:35:25.640 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:35:25.640 --> 00:35:27.050 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: That's a lovely area.

00:35:27.050 --> 00:35:29.008 align:middle line:84%
Not that I'm trying to
bring more people there.

00:35:29.008 --> 00:35:31.910 align:middle line:84%
But the thing is that
the people are still

00:35:31.910 --> 00:35:34.650 align:middle line:84%
there because when they died
before they left the body,

00:35:34.650 --> 00:35:36.590 align:middle line:84%
they would say, well,
what does the tribe need

00:35:36.590 --> 00:35:38.900 align:middle line:90%
for its continuous development?

00:35:38.900 --> 00:35:41.115 align:middle line:84%
Because it's a place where
not much water exists,

00:35:41.115 --> 00:35:41.915 align:middle line:90%
for one thing.

00:35:41.915 --> 00:35:42.170 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:35:42.170 --> 00:35:43.620 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: So they
would say, well,

00:35:43.620 --> 00:35:45.520 align:middle line:84%
we need more rain because
otherwise the crops

00:35:45.520 --> 00:35:46.320 align:middle line:90%
are going to fail.

00:35:46.320 --> 00:35:48.778 align:middle line:84%
So when they die, the spirit
goes back into the other world

00:35:48.778 --> 00:35:51.540 align:middle line:84%
and literally, within
minutes, it starts raining.

00:35:51.540 --> 00:35:53.737 align:middle line:84%
So they're in the elements
of the actual place,

00:35:53.737 --> 00:35:55.320 align:middle line:84%
and I just love
hanging out with them.

00:35:55.320 --> 00:35:56.870 align:middle line:84%
So just because
you're dead doesn't

00:35:56.870 --> 00:35:57.955 align:middle line:90%
mean you can't be useful.

00:35:57.955 --> 00:35:58.755 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:35:58.755 --> 00:36:01.740 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And so and Wupatki
Canyon, that's another place.

00:36:01.740 --> 00:36:03.990 align:middle line:84%
There's a cliff dwelling
there, which I love going to.

00:36:03.990 --> 00:36:06.067 align:middle line:84%
Now that you have to
go on a guided tour

00:36:06.067 --> 00:36:07.650 align:middle line:84%
because you became
a bit more popular.

00:36:07.650 --> 00:36:10.700 align:middle line:84%
But if you get to
know the people there

00:36:10.700 --> 00:36:13.852 align:middle line:84%
